@ericcbarnes I'm sure you can understand the difference between tarrifs collected on imported goods, vs an income tax levied on individuals as codified by 16A. Not sure how foreign tax laws are relevant. I'm quite a fan of tarrifs, but utterly despise income taxation.

@ericcbarnes You didn't ask a question -- more of a demand. You're also wrong: the first (temporary) federal income tax wasn't levied until 1861. The annual, eternal income tax came in 1915. It hasn't always been this way, and it's possible to go back.
